rename.from: affine grid and grid sample support
rename.to: affine grid and grid sample support in onnxruntime

body:
There is GridSample contrib operator in ONNX Runtime (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/8551), so I think it is available to use as long as you can export your model using pytorch custom op: [example](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/47435311f43cf587b40da20dc33d94bbf950e1d4/onnxruntime/python/tools/pytorch_export_contrib_ops.py#L36-L62)

GridSample was added to onnx in Nov (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/3557). The operator definition will be available in onnx 1.11 release. PyTorch will need some time to support export the operator.
@tianleiwu When onnx 1.11 version will be release with GridSample features ?

@jcwchen, do you know when onnx 1.11 will be released?
Note that, after the operator spec in onnx, there still need some time (I guess a few months) to add support in ONNX Runtime and PyTorch exporter.

> @jcwchen, do you know when onnx 1.11 will be released?

ONNX will release 1.11 in the week of 2/7.

> @jcwchen, do you know when onnx 1.11 will be released? Note that, after the operator spec in onnx, there still need some time (I guess a few months) to add support in ONNX Runtime and PyTorch exporter.

@tianleiwu, is there any way to do/build it manually?

This issue has been automatically marked as stale due to inactivity and will be closed in 7 days if no further activity occurs. If further support is needed, please provide an update and/or more details.

**Environment**
Onnx-> 1.11.0
torch -> 1.11.0+cu102
torchvision  -> 0.12.0+cu102

I am trying to convert my Pytorch model to ONNX using above environment versions. still getting same error like - 


**RuntimeError: Exporting the operator grid_sampler to ONNX opset version 11 is not supported. Please feel free to request support or submit a pull request on PyTorch GitHub.**

I have verified that `4D grid_sample` works correctly in an informal way.

1. PyTorch v1.12.0-dev
2. onnxruntime v1.12.0-dev - opset=16

- Manually applied patches
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/76159

- PyTorch build
  https://zenn.dev/pinto0309/scraps/a9cf414ef289e7

- onnxruntime build
  https://zenn.dev/pinto0309/scraps/9e3b1f98ba6bd4

I have been following the issue related to grid sampler from very long, and my main interest is because I want to export STN layer  to onnx.

based on issue I found that ONNX opset 16 supports grid sample hence I followed @PINTO0309 links to build pytorch and ONNX, I was able to use opset 16 however I get this issue:

````
Exporting the operator ::affine_grid_generator to ONNX opset version 16 is not supported
````

Please help me understand how do I track this issue, what onnx version and pytorch version might support it.

Hello ,

https://github.com/PINTO0309/openvino2tensorflow/releases

You guys just build it yourselves. The `affine_grid_generator` is not implemented in onnx and is not available at this time.
